commentPostTextItems.html: It is all over, Sri Lanka win by 106 runs!
This has been a remarkable performance by the home team, they have secured their place in the final
By beating the Kiwis with such a wide margin, the net run rate situation might look much better for the Indians.
Vaas bowled a brilliant opening spell picking up three quick wickets and ripping through the Kiwi batting
Fernando who was rewarded by Jayasuriya for some fiery bowling in this ODI series. He shared the new ball with Vaas and troubled every batsman with sheer pace and bounce
Kiwis were never really in the match. They finished with 115/9
The last pair of Mills and Tuffey added 32 valuable runs in 5.3 overs.
This has been the most convincing performance by the Sri Lankans in the tournament so far. They take on India tomorrow right here at the Sinhalese Sports Club ground.
The Man of the Match is Chaminda Vaas!
India will have to win tomorrow to stay in the tournament. They will come out blazing against Sri Lanka tomorrow.
Catch up all the live action right here on www.cricinfo.com
The match is scheduled to start at 1000 Hrs Local time, 0930 Hrs IST, 0400 Hrs GMT

stories.title: They just destroyed us in the first ten overs: Fleming
stories.summary:
After a disappointing performance by New Zealand, the Kiwi captain
Stephen Fleming still remained positive about his side's chances of
making it to the Coca-Cola Cup final

stories.title: Sri Lanka overpower New Zealand to secure place in final
stories.summary:
Sri Lanka booked themselves a guaranteed berth in the final of the
Coca Cola Cup with an overwhelming 106-run victory over New Zealand at
the Sinhalese Sports Club in Colombo today
